bench_03 round56 — COLUMN-SUBSPACE BAGGING (K=10) vs SEED-AVG (K=10) vs base-08 (ALL 16)  [OFFLINE]
==============================================================================

SETUP:
  base    == shipped 08: HGB, early_stopping, cat_mask=object cols,
             seed-0, full train, FULL columns.
  colbag  == column-subspace bagging K=10. Per k in 0..9: choose
             ceil(0.8*n_feat) feature columns WITHOUT replacement via
             RandomState(k), fit an identical base-08 HGB
             (random_state=k) on ALL rows but only those columns
             (cat_mask rebuilt for the subset), predict_proba on the
             SAME test columns; aggregate = MEAN of the valid-k proba
             vectors. l2/msl are the base-08 gate values from the FULL
             train (NOT recomputed on the subset). tiny n_feat
             (ceil>=n_feat) -> member uses ALL columns.
             GUARD: single-class member -> that k skipped.
  seedavg == plain seed-avg K=10: fit K base-08 HGB on the FULL train,
             FULL columns, random_state 0..9, MEAN of proba.
  Single new mechanism vs seedavg = COLUMN-subspace diversity.

